HEADWORD: Graafian
<hw>Graaf"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or discovered by, <person>Regnier de
<etsep>Graaf</etsep></person>, a Dutch physician.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Graafian follicles</b></col><cd> or vesicles, small
cavities in which the ova are developed in the ovaries of mammals, and
by the bursting of which they are discharged.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graal</ent>⟦br⟧
